FBIS4-13084 "drnes074_r_94006" FBIS-NES-94-074 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 India Officials, Parties React to Signing of GATT Accord Officials, Parties React to Signing of GATT Accord Minister `Strongly' Defends GATT Accord BK1804130494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 GMT 18 Apr 94 BK1804130494 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The commerce minister has strongly justified India signing the new GATT deal, saying the opposition stand is based on narrow partisan considerations. Mr. Pranab Mukherji, who returned to New Delhi from Marrakesh this morning, said there is no rationale in the demand for opting out of the global trading system. He pointed out that 20 more countries want to join the new trade agreement in addition to the 125 countries which are signatories to it.
